This paper deals with the problem of computing the values of simple stochastic games, which is a topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science > Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also presents algorithms that rely on computational techniques such as exhaustive search and successive improvements, which are common in areas such as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of linear programming, which is a technique commonly used in optimization problems and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the concept of positional strategies, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
